	   	 <td colspan="3"><strong>How do I sign up?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">Visit Paywithfriends.com and click the “Join Now” button in the top left corner. You need a valid email address, a unique username and a password. Passwords are case sensitive, so be careful typing your new password. Choose the right username because it will be displayed on your public profile!
<br>
<br>
<strong>How do I setup my Amazon Payments to receive payments?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">Setting your Amazon Payments accounts is required to receive payments. It's required one a year and it is easy to setup! Make sure you're logged into you Paywithfriends account. 
<br>On your account page, review and check the “I accept the Paywithfriends terms and conditions.” 
Click on the “Set Up Amazon Payments.” <br> Then just follow these 5 easy simple steps to activate your Amazon Payments account to process payments:
<br> 1. Sign in using your existing Amazon account or create a new one
<br> 2. Accept commission agreement with Paywithfriends
<br> 3. You’ll be requested to re-login to Amazon 
<br> 4. Authorize Paywithfriends to process payments to your Amazon Payments account
<br> 5. Confirm your account
<br>You are now ready to accept Amazon Payments via Paywithfriends for up to one year.
Please review Amazon policies to make sure that your trade category is accepted.

	  <br>
<br>
<strong>How do I add an item for a group purchase?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">Visit your account page. Click on “Add Item”. The next page allows you to describe and price an item you want to add. 
<br>- Select the “Buy in group as a shopper”. 
<br>- Provide a title for the item and a price. 
<br>- Include any fees for shipping or other costs.
<br>- Also include an estimate of the Paywithfriends, and Amazon fees. Consider also whether your friends will incur fees from international charge cards.
<br>- Select a category from the drop down menu.
<br>- Provide the URL where the item is for sale. 
<br>- You can also upload the item photo if you want to but it’s not required.
<br>- Provide your contact information for the item (email and phone number) to receive order confirmations and let your friends contact you if they have questions.
<br>- Provide the geographic location of the item.
<br>- Click the “add item” button to post the item on Paywithfriends.
<br>- Your item page will be available for sale for seven days according to the Amazon Payments policies.
<br>Read more about their policies at http://payments.amazon.com.

<br><br>
<strong>How do I manage or change the items I posted?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">You can edit or delete items you posted anytime. Log in to your account, go to your account page and click the "Manage Item" button.
<br>
To edit or view an existing item that you posted, select the item from the drop down menu and click the "edit/view" button. The item will be displayed on all the forms below. Simply update the information and click on “Save changes” to publish your updates. Hit “cancel” if you don’t want to publish the updates.
You can also delete an item by selecting it from the drop down menu and click the delete button.

<br><br>
<strong>How do I make a partial payment for the item I posted?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">When you add an item, you'll have the opportunity to view it afterwards. Before you can invite your friends to contribute, you'll need to make a partial payment for the item you posted. 
<br>Click the "Paywithfriends button" on your item page to travel to the co-branded Paywithfriends/Amazon Payments login page. Log in to Amazon Payments account, review that your payment is correct, and click “Confirm.” 
<br>You'll be taken to the partial payment confirmation page. You will also receive a partial payment email with the details of your payment. Forward it to invite your friends to contribute!

<br> <br> 	<strong>How can I promote my items and invite my friends to contribute?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">By letting people know! Invite your friends by forwarding your partial payment email or share your item listings page. <br>Ask your friends to forward the Paywithfriends purchase invitation email to other interested friends. 
Or simply copy and paste the URL of the item posted or use the “Share” button below the photo on an item page to post the item on your personal page, blog or any social network like Facebook, Twitter or Myspace. 
Your friends add their payment contribution using the Amazon Account within 7 days you posted the item.

<br> <br> 	<strong>How do I receive the money after everyone's contributed?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">Once you have raised the money from your friends, the funds are immediately available in your Amazon Payments account so you can buy the item for everyone.  
<br> The funds are available on the credit card or debit card you selected when you setup your Amazon Payments account to receive payments. During the setup you can also elect to receive payments directly to your bank account. The time it takes for the transfer to be credited to your account depends on your banks policies. 
 
<br> <br> 	<strong>How do I contribute to buy the item that my friend posted on Paywithfriends?</td>
       </tr>
	   <tr>
	   	 <td colspan="3">You don't need to be a member of Paywithfriends in order to buy an item that my friend posted. You only need to add your contribution using your Amazon account. Visit your friend's item page, add your payment, name, and email to the item page. Click Paywithfriends! 

 <br> <br> 	<strong>How do I check my transaction history on Paywithfriends?</td>
       </tr>
